    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_501584">what do you think about the oil spill?  what do you think about the fact that many ecosystems, livelihoods, tourist destinations, communities and towns are being ruined?  how does it make you feel that our president doesn't seem to give a damn?  what do you think about the never-ending tax breaks that oil companies receive from our US government, and the fact that the people who are supposed to be overseeing the safety, procedures and conduct of the oil companies are also having drug fueled sex parties with each other (i'm not joking).  <br />
<br />
- as a side note, they still get to keep their jobs.  but we live in fear of the idea that our boss might know we play a certain specific computer game online?  which is worse, really?  well, those cocaine fueled sex addicts are still getting paid.  handsomely.  -<br />
<br />
and how does it make you feel when the our right to know how bad things really are is taken away?  the media is blocked from covering vast portions of the oil spill in the name of safety.  in the name of total bull ****.  <br />
<br />

