    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_501593">ITT the entire government is a borg collective, the only reason things don't change is because the president doesn't care about a zillion gallon oil spill!<br />
<br />
I love it when people simplify like, 500,000 different political views in the government and hand pick the ones that reinforce their belief that the government don't care about them and use that to represent every individual.<br />
<br />
Of course the President cares. He's not a God, he's not going to be able to come up with a solution all by himself when no one else can. I mean really. People have some pretty amazingly unrealistic expectations. The guy has about 10 trillion issues to deal with right now, and the oil thing is just a higher priority one. But nobody has a solution, so why is anyone surprised it's not solved?<br />
<br />
Even if someone comes up with a solution, there's red tape everywhere, people blocking the solution for their own benefit, or for their parties' benefit. That is not a sign of indifference.<br />
<br />
The oil spill is a train wreck that nobody knows how to stop. All that can be done now is to move forward. The government, contrary to popular belief, does not have the power to collectively bitch slap one of the biggest corporates in the world.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
