    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_501603">From the point of view of someone who's not affected by this: it's pretty ****ed up situation when the person who seems like they'd have the best track record (or at least not one filled with ****up and incompetence) and experience to help with the situation and not make things worse is a Hollywood director.<br />
<br />
All kidding aside though, a spill of that magnitude it just doesn't feel like BP's been treating it nearly as seriously as it should be. Honestly when we read about this stuff we just go &quot;Jeez, it's like Katrina with oil&quot;. The stories about the safety violations and lack of plans or ability to do something about spills at this depth have however had the positive effect here that the fishing industry has made some very firm demands that laws to insure this does not happen here go into effect BEFORE anyone's allowed to even test what may be an oil rich deep sea area near us.</div>
