    <div align="left" id="post_message_501731">While I don't deny the world is going to **** - Stalk is right. Things weren't better back then, you're just looking through rose-colored glasses. What exactly was better?<br />
<br />
20s - Prohibition and rampant gang activity because of it<br />
30s - That whole stock market crash thingy<br />
40s - Not sure, but I think there was some war we were involved in....<br />
50s &amp; 60s - I bet the McCarthy era was a real treat<br />
70s - Another war we were involved in....lots of people were happy about this one right?!<br />
80s - Crack epidemic and soaring murder rates<br />
<br />
<br />
I bet the people living during those period felt the same way - the world is ending, society is crumbling, etc.<br />
<br />
And to think that at any point in the history of the WORLD that money wasn't the number one motivator for countries and individuals alike....well thats quite the fantasy world you thought up there....</div>
